Peculiar FC were crowned winners of the 2022 edition of the Iyk Madu Obi Ramadan Cup after they beat Bariga Professional in a six-goal thriller. David Dimaku was the match hero after scoring a brace in the 4-2 win our Bariga Professional, as the one-month long grassroot football championship was decided on Sunday  at the proposed palace ground (Sansan Field) in Igando.   God knows everything about my career, says newly-wed Noble     Pepsi, Guinness back World Corporate Golf Challenge     Knocks trail Nigeria’s withdrawal from global…   Sponsor of the tournament and Evergreen Group Chief Executive Officer (CEO) Chief Iyk Madu Obi was among the VIPs present for the final, which lived up to the hype. Peculiar FC who were semi-finalists in the last edition, did the damage within 14 minutes after taking the game to Bariga Professional and in the 20th minute, they got the reward for their good play scoring the opening goal with a sublime finish from Dimaku. Dimaku then made it 2-0, capitalizing from a school boy defending to put the ball past a helpless Bariga Professional goalkeeper while Etim Osuyak scored  his team’s third goal from a goal mouth scramble four minutes to end the first half. However, Bariga Professional stepped up their game as they got the better of the second half after Ogbeyi Solomon scored two quick goals to set up what looked like a possible comeback but it was little too late  as Kehinde  soon scored the fourth goal for Peculiar FC.